24
) maxillary teeth present, small.

The condition of the oblique lateral stripe is variable among specimens, from a series of light spots/ blotches extending diagonally from the groin across the flanks and barely reaching the level of the insertion of the arm ( e.g.
IRSNB 1986
) to an almost solid, clearly visible stripe extending diagonally from the groin across the flanks to the level of the insertion of the arm, then breaking in a series of light spots almost reaching the eye ( e.g.
ROM 39638
). Slight variation also occurs between the right and the left flank.
